title: Tridium Niagara Station: Fuel Tank
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/environment
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check reads the fuel tank consumption and level of a Tridium Niagara
 station from .1.3.6.1.4.1.4131.1.6.15.1.1.3. Detection fires when the
 device sysObjectID starts with .1.3.6.1.4.1.4131.1.

 The remaining litres are computed from the consumption reading plus a
 fixed tank size of 6000 litres. Lower WARN/CRIT levels on the remaining
 litres can be configured via the rule "Tridium Fuel"; the service goes
 {WARN} or {CRIT} when the remaining amount drops at or below them. The
 check reports the metrics {usage}, {last_cons} and {level}.

discovery:
 One service is created when the fuel tree is present on the device.
